        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 9:19AM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 919 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Mccormick County Airport, or 14 miles south of
Greenwood, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Batesburg-Leesville, Edgefield, Saluda, McCormick, Johnston, Ridge
Spring, Saluda County Airport, Edgefield County Airport, Elijah Clark
State Park, Mccormick County Airport, Monetta, Trenton, Bradley,
Parksville, Ward, Plum Branch, Strom Thurmond High School, Saluda Co
Sheriff's Office, Good Hope, and Northside Fire Station Main.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
